  "output": "Now let me deliver the full coverage analysis.\n\n# Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: zero automated tests exist anywhere in the repo** (no `tests/`, no `pytest`/`unittest` in the venv, no CI config). Everything below is new coverage, organized by module, ordered roughly by risk × blast radius. Setup needed once:\n\n```\npip install pytest pytest-asyncio respx   # respx mocks httpx at the transport layer\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. `models.py` — highest priority (everything downstream depends on `parse_posted_at` and `Job.key`)\n\n### Gaps\n- `parse_posted_at`: no tests for ms-vs-sec epoch boundary, negative/garbage strings, `Z`-suffix ISO, naive-vs-aware datetimes, empty string, non-digit garbage that isn't valid ISO either.\n- `Job.key` / `content_hash`: no test that key is stable across unrelated field changes but hash changes on title/location/url/department changes.\n- `Job.to_row`: no test that `raw` is dropped and `key`/`content_hash` are injected.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_ms_epoch_lever_style(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt == datetime.fromtimestamp(1643241332, tz=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_sec_epoch(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is timezone.utc\n\n    def test_epoch_boundary_just_under_1e12_is_seconds(self):\n        # 999999999999 (12 digits) must NOT be divided by 1000\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"999999999999\")\n        assert dt.year > 33000  # sanity: treated as seconds, not ms\n\n    def test_negative_epoch(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"-100\").tzinfo is not None\n\n    def test_iso_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt == datetime(2026, 1, 15, 10, 0, tzinfo=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_iso_naive_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2026-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_workday_prose_is_unparseable(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_garbage_string(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not-a-date\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                    title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        base.update(kw)\n        return Job(**base)\n\n    def test_key_stable_across_cosmetic_changes(self):\n        j1 = self._job(title=\"Engineer I\")\n        j2 = self._job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert j1.key == j2.key  # same source/company/external_id\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self):\n        j1 = self._job(title=\"Engineer I\")\n        j2 = self._job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_when_unrelated_field_changes(self):\n        j1 = self._job(salary_range=\"$100k\")\n        j2 = self._job(salary_range=\"$200k\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash  # salary isn't in the hash blob\n\n    def test_to_row_drops_raw_injects_key_and_hash(self):\n        j = self._job(raw={\"secret\": True})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filters.py`\n\n### Gaps\n- Word-boundary regex behavior (`\\bC\\b` vs substring \"C++\" or \"React\"-in-\"Reactor\") — untested and plausibly wrong for short/symbol-heavy keywords.\n- `cutoff` \"keep if unparseable\" behavior — the one deliberately forgiving branch, unasserted.\n- Empty/`None` rule lists (falsy vs missing key).\n- Case-insensitivity